introduction:

I am Pragya Singh, currently pursuing an Integrated MCA in AI from Parul University with a CGPA of 7.76.

I have strong interest in full-stack development and AI-powered applications. I have built projects like PrepMind AI, which is a full-stack platform that generates exam notes using Gemini API and also integrates Stripe payments.

I have experience working with the MERN stack and deploying applications. I enjoy building real-world projects and improving problem-solving skills.

Currently, I am focusing on strengthening my DSA and backend skills to become a job-ready full-stack developer.

Project: 

PrepMind AI is an AI-powered exam notes generator built using MERN stack.

Users can upload content or enter topics, and the system uses Gemini API to generate structured notes.

On the backend, Node.js handles API requests and integrates with Gemini API. MongoDB stores user data and generated notes.

I also implemented Stripe for payment handling, allowing users to unlock premium features.

One challenge I faced was managing API response delays, which I solved using proper error handling and loading states.